Your dropping tube does not work. 
Followed exactly all the steps and no solution drops fell into the testing plate. I had to squeeze harder and harderr until I did it so strongly that the tamp spilt the solution. 
Self-tests for inexperienced people should be very very easy. Otherwise, we're just gonna expend money and waste tests.

snippet.textDisplay: I did this test 2 times already. The same problem occurred. The 1st time was on my husband. Did this on the 2nd time on myself just now. There were no droplets. So i removed the tamp and put it back on real quick because a foam was getting released from the tip. So I dropped the foams on the test. It’s negative. It seems that firstly The tamp should not be pushed too far or it needs an oxygen? On my husbands test there was also foam but Ican’t remember how it really happened. I onky remember that I waited for a bot more and then squeezed. My husband’s was positive. It was done on the 1st January. Mine is negative now.
